item.title: The Sacrifice Comic: Part One
item.dc:creator: Acristoff
item.description:
dagrox94:

There seems to be an issue with the storyline from the comic and the storyline from the game… In the comic, the survivors raise the bridge, get on a boat, and get the hell outta there. In the Sacrifice DLC, The survivors raise the bridge and it cuts off there. In the Passing, they are… still hanging around the bridge? What? Why?

As you can see in the comic they leave when the weather clears up, they already mentioned they were going to wait it out on the bridge for a bit as well. And I can imagine zoey has no problem helping other survivors do their thing as mentioned heavily by the comic and the game. And with the generator up to full gas they have the means to bring it back up and down for a good long while.

The end.

Read full topic

item.title: The Sacrifice Comic: Part One
item.dc:creator: saivert
item.description:
yeah. seems like The Passing was from the L4D2 point of view while The Sacrifice is from the L4D1 point of view. Both stories converge in this one.
Then you have the comic which ties in the blanks inbetween and fills in the back story somewhat. But the comic was also confusing they seem to jump back in time a lot.

item.title: The Sacrifice Comic: Part One
item.dc:creator: saivert
item.description:
I will play this tomorrow or two days from now. Seems like it is impossible to create a new game from the lobby now since it can’t find a server to play on. Everybody tries to play it at the same time hammering Valve’s servers. But this is expected with every new big release from Valve.

I tried hosting it myself (I got 15/15 Mbps connection which should be more than enough) and two of the players had a latency of 200ms (ping). How they got into my lobby I don’t know. I don’t want asshats from australia (or somewhere else on the other side of the globe) in my lobby when I’m living in Norway. Fix the stupid matchmaking.
